<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Less XP loss is absolute BS</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:37 p.m. 25/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Less XP loss is absolute BS<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2087" TARGET=_self>50% less exp loss at death</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Damn I hate whiners. EQ is hard, but not impossible. Now it is getting easier. The more whiners complain about how hard the game is the easier it's gonna get. I for one like a challenge. This game, even with the increasing large XP loss, is very challenging. It hasn't lost too much of its challenge from the change in XP loss, but I hope this is where it stops. Dying is supposed to suck(You know, DEATH). XP loss is about the only thing you could lose that makes you want to not die. If there where no XP loss people would be training SG without sow. The game would be absolutely retarded. Why don't you quite whining to Verant about how you die to much and learn how not to die.

<P>btw:I have died twice just helping my friend retrieve a corpse. It is frustrating, but I could have taken more precautions to prevent it(and will in the future). The main thing is, the game shouldn't change because I make some incompetent moves. It shouldn't if you do either.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
